========,1,preface.
Leota Township is a township in Nobles County, Minnesota, United States.
The population was 463 at the 2000 census.
Within the township is the CDP of Leota.
========,2,Geography.
According to the United States Census Bureau, the township has a total area of 36.2 square miles (93.7 km²), all of it land.
The main geographic feature in Leota Townships is the Champepadan Creek.
